<item>
            <title>[AMQ-2290] Memory leak in SelectorParser LRUCache</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-2290</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There appears to be a memory leak in the LRUCache used by the SelectorParser. We have a simple selector-based request/response implementation which means we create a new selector on every request and these appear to be sticking around despite the use of an LRUCache with a 10,000 entry limit. A quick look at the LRUCache code didn&apos;t reveal any obvious problems, so I&apos;m not sure what&apos;s going on here. For the time being we are rolling back to 5.2. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
